We recommended and Management has agreed that:

a. The Inventory Committee to establish the existence, accuracy and completeness of the Municipality's PPE by conducting a physical inventory at least once a year, and prepare and submit the RPCPPE pursuant to Section 124, Volume I of MNGAS for LGUs;


b. The Municipal Accountant and GSO In-Charge to maintain and regularly update their respective PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards;


c. The Municipal Accountant and GSO In-Charge to perform reconciliation of the reported PPEs per RPCPPE with the accounting and property records; and


d. We likewise recommended that the Management consider conducting a one-time cleansing of PPE accounts pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020- 006 to finally establish the balance of PPE in the books.

We recommended and the OIC - Municipal Treasurer’s Office agreed to:            

a. Intensify its collection efforts to collect the receivables on stall rental fees;   

b. Ensure the correctness and propriety of information provided in the Contracts of Lease such as the name of stall holder, stall location, and the monthly rate in accordance with the Municipality's Revenue Code, and make certain that these are renewed and issued to all stall holders upon expiration;

c. Maintain an updated Master List of Stall Occupants showing the names of stall holders, stall location, monthly fees, and outstanding balances (current and prior years) including surcharges as appropriate, for proper monitoring and timely decision making; and

d. Facilitate the creation of a permanent Market Committee pursuant to the Revenue Code of the Municipality to hasten the restoration of closed stalls and make it available to other tenants.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to designate a responsible official to facilitate the processing of the Certificate of Title of all the lands owned by the Municipality to establish absolute ownership and protect the interest of the Municipality over those properties.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to: 

Create an Appraisal Committee composed of the OIC - Municipal Assessor, Engineer, Accountant, and Treasurer to facilitate the appraisal of the value of the parcels of land owned by the Municipality;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to record in the books of account the unrecorded land properties of the Municipality;


Xxx

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to appropriate budget for the subdivision of lots.

We recommended and Management agreed to the following:

a. The concerned officials to discontinue the practice of granting cash advances for confidential funds for periods exceeding three months, ensure that the cash advance is not utilized to reimburse expenses incurred prior to the granting thereof, and strictly adhere to Items 6.1.2 and 6.1.5 of COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01;

b.  The certifying officials to indicate the date of signing the DV and releasing of check to the payee to properly identify the reckoning date of submission of the cash advance DV and its supporting documents to the Office of the Auditor;

c. The Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking documents to the Office of the Auditor, pursuant to Items 6.1.7 and 6.1.8 of COA-DBM- DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01; and

d. The Municipal Accountant to immediately submit to the Office of the Auditor, the cash advance vouchers for the confidential fund, its transmittal letter and supporting documents in a sealed envelope within 7 days from the release of the check, in accordance with Item 6.1.8.4 of COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01.

We recommended and the Human Resource Management Office, Municipal Accountant, and concerned offices agreed to:

Maintain a manpower database to effectively account and monitor its personnel complement and ensure that all outsourced workers are covered with a binding contract and/or other appropriate documents;

Formulate policies/guidelines in engaging and managing outsourced workers and in the granting of wages and allowances.

