Recommendations
We recommended and Management agreed to direct the MENRO Designate and concerned personnel to:
Actively promote and enforce the sorting and segregation of wastes at the household level and all other sources;
Ensure that collection of biodegradable/compostable and reusable/recyclable wastes is being done at the barangay level and only non-recyclable materials and special wastes shall be collected pursuant to pertinent provisions of Section 10 of RA No. 9003;
Establish a policy for the generation of revenue from saleable recyclables and include the same in the Municipal Revenue Code;
Review and update its 10-year SWM Plan and prepare a comprehensive work and financial plan relative to solid waste management operations to establish the timing and extent of implementation of each program, project and activities during the year, and to employ monitoring mechanisms to ensure full implementation thereof.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to designate a responsible official to facilitate the processing of the Certificate of Title of all the lands owned by the Municipality to establish absolute ownership and protect the interest of the Municipality over those properties.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:

Create an Appraisal Committee composed of the OIC - Municipal Assessor, Engineer, Accountant, and Treasurer to facilitate the appraisal of the value of the parcels of land owned by the Municipality;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to record in the books of account the unrecorded land properties of the Municipality;



Direct the Municipal Accountant to maintain Property, Plant, and Equipment Ledger Cards for all properties owned by the Municipality; 





Direct the designated General Services Officer to maintain Property Cards for all the properties owned by the Municipality; and

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to appropriate budget for the subdivision of lots.

