We recommended that the LCE direct the following:
Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory count of all properties and take on the responsibilities as prescribed under Section 124 of MNGAS;
Municipal Accountant and GSO to prepare and update the PPE ledger cards and property cards, respectively, for proper identification of all PPE;
Personnel responsible to prepare the RPCPPE and reconcile the balances between the Accounting and General Services Office; and
Creation of an Appraisal Committee to assist in the disposal of unserviceable properties; the person responsible to submit the IIRUP to the COA Office as required in the guidelines; and thereafter, the Accounting Office to record journal entries for the dropping of PPEs from the books of accounts once the unserviceable properties were properly disposed.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the concerned officials and employees to take immediate actions on the matters listed below:
Facilitate the timely request of funds in order to deliver quality implementation of projects and activities; ensure that budget allocation for GAD is fully utilized in providing adequate facilities and resources; and formulate/propose other programs/activities relevant to the projects and with long-term favorable effect to the constituents;
Ensure that the GAD Focal Point System is fully-functional and the members have the capacity and influence to promote gender mainstreaming pursuant to Section 37 of the MCW IRR;
Maintain and update the GAD Database that will serve as basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation that will support the LGU’s efforts in promoting, protecting and fulfilling women’s human rights, economic empowerment and gender-responsive governance towards the attainment of gender equality and women’s empowerment;
Ensure submission of the Annual GAD Plan and Budget and GAD Accomplishment Report in required format to the DILG Regional Office VI for review and approval to ascertain compliance with the guidelines; and
Strictly adhere to the provisions of JMC No. 2013-01 of the PCW, DILG, DBM and NEDA.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the LCE direct the concerned officials and employees to take immediate actions on the matters listed below:
a.) 	Ensure that their GAD GFPS is fully-functional and the members have the capacity and influence to promote gender mainstreaming pursuant to Section 37 of the MCW IRR;
b.) 	Set-up and maintain a GAD Database that will serve as basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation; and formulate GAD Codes or Ordinances that will support the Municipality’s efforts in promoting, protecting and fulfilling women’s human rights, economic empowerment and gender-responsive governance towards the attainment of gender equality and women’s empowerment;
c.) 	Ensure submission of the Annual GPB and GAD Accomplishment Report (AR) in required format to the DILG RO VI for review and approval to ascertain compliance with the guidelines;
d.) 	Propose plans/ programs for GAD, PWDs and the Youth to maximize the utilization of funds and benefits thereof and ensure that the relevant PPAs and GAD activities will address/respond to the gender issues identified; and
e.) 	Strictly adhere to the provisions of JMC No. 2013-01 of the PCW, DILG, DBM and NEDA.

We recommended that the LCE direct the concerned officials and employees      in-charge/assigned in the implementation of the SWM Program in the Municipality to adhere strictly to the provisions of RA No. 9003.
We also recommended the following:
Ensure that the collection schedule for specific types of wastes shall cover all the barangays in the Municipality;
Coordinate with Barangay Officials regarding information dissemination/ campaign on proper segregation and disposal of wastes to be implemented in their barangay;
Make representation with the Sangguniang Bayan (SB) for the revision of the Ordinance relative to the rates of garbage fees.
